@startuml steering_turn_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Steering Turn Signal Flow\n(Input_Console -> ESC -> MDPS -> CGW / ADAS / CLU)

actor "Driver\n(Input Console)" as Driver #F4F7FB
participant "Input_Console\nVehicle > Steering" as Panel #E8F0FE
participant "ESC\nmanual steering bridge" as ESC #FFE6E6
participant "MDPS\nsteering state producer" as MDPS #E8F7E8
participant "CGW\nfreshness/gateway view" as CGW #FFF4CC
participant "ADAS\nsteering consumer" as ADAS #FCE8FF
participant "CLU\nwheel frame output" as CLU #E8F0FE

== Manual Steering Input ==

Driver -> Panel : Drag steering bar / wheel
activate Panel
Panel -> Panel : Write Cmd::steeringAngleCmd\nrange -540..+540 deg
note right of Panel
Input seam
- Cmd::steeringAngleCmd
- donor/readback UI also watches
  Chassis::steeringAngle and
  Display::steeringFrame
end note
deactivate Panel

== ESC Manual Readback Bridge ==

activate ESC
Panel -> ESC : Cmd::steeringAngleCmd (sysvar)
ESC -> ESC : mapSignedSteeringCmdToLegacyAngle()
ESC -> ESC : publishManualSteeringReadback()
ESC -> ESC : deriveManualSteeringInputFromAngle()
note right of ESC
Manual mode condition:
- Test::scenarioActiveId == 0

Effects:
- Chassis::steeringAngle = 0..138
- steeringInput = 0 or 1
end note
ESC -> CLU : Chassis::steeringAngle (sysvar readback)
deactivate ESC

== MDPS Steering Publish ==

activate MDPS
ESC -> MDPS : frmSteeringCanMsg\nor manual Chassis::steeringAngle
MDPS -> MDPS : deriveManualSteeringInputFromAngle()\nwhen manual mode
MDPS -> MDPS : steeringAngleRaw = steeringInput * 30
MDPS -> MDPS : steeringTorque = steeringInput * 20
MDPS -> CGW : frmSteeringStateCanMsg
MDPS -> ADAS : frmSteeringStateCanMsg
MDPS -> MDPS : output frmSteeringTorqueMsg
note right of MDPS
Published every 50 ms:
- frmSteeringStateCanMsg
- frmSteeringTorqueMsg
- frmEpsStateMsg
- backbone steering state
end note
deactivate MDPS

== Downstream Consumers ==

activate CGW
CGW -> CGW : update gSteeringTsMs\nand steering freshness age
note right of CGW
Gateway side effect:
- steering freshness merged into
  chassis visibility / health view
end note
deactivate CGW

activate ADAS
ADAS -> ADAS : gCanSteeringInput = SteeringState
ADAS -> ADAS : steeringInputNorm /\nAB-group / release logic
note right of ADAS
Used by:
- decel release logic
- zone/speed adjustment
- steer group detection
end note
deactivate ADAS

activate CLU
CLU -> CLU : if manual -> use Cmd::steeringAngleCmd
CLU -> CLU : else -> use Chassis::steeringAngle
CLU -> CLU : frame = (angle * 69 + 69) / 138
CLU -> Panel : Display::steeringFrame
note right of CLU
Display seam:
- Display::steeringFrame 0..69
- wheel image follows the bar
end note
deactivate CLU

== Visible User Outcome ==

Driver <- Panel : Steering bar, degree box,\nwheel image move together

note over Driver, CLU
Representative runtime chain
1. Input_Console writes Cmd::steeringAngleCmd
2. ESC creates manual steering readback
3. MDPS publishes steering state / torque
4. CGW and ADAS consume steering state
5. CLU renders steeringFrame for donor wheel image
end note

@enduml
